<TEXT>
Police seek
gang of four
DETECTIVES are seeking a gang of four, aged between 18 and 20, who stabbed two
men in an apparently motiveless attack in Ruchazie, Glasgow, about 1am
yesterday.
One man suffered six stab wounds on his arms, legs, and the left side of his
chest. The second man was stabbed in the inner left thigh. Both are in stable
condition at Glasgow Royal Infirmary. Anyone with information on the attack is
asked to contact police at Easterhouse on 0141.532.4300.
Incinerator order
AN incinerator which burns half of Scotland's clinical waste has failed a
Government pollution test for the fourth time this year. Dundee District
Council said yesterday defective monitoring equipment at the Baldovie
incinerator would be replaced before the February 16 deadline imposed by
inspectors.
Pedestrian killed
POLICE have appealed for witnesses after the death of a 53-year-old pedestrian
who was struck by a car in London Road, Edinburgh, yesterday morning. He was
Frederick McCardle, of Loganlea Loan, Edinburgh.
Jury discharged
THE jury in the trial of a man accused of a neighbour's murder in a row over a
barking dog was discharged yesterday after failing to reach a verdict. Nicholas
Farnell, 32, of Hampshire, now faces a retrial at Winchester Crown Court.
Police apology
A POLICE chief yesterday apologised to a family in North Yorkshire for a
bungled raid in which the family was held at gunpoint. Police are considering
laying charges against a man who allegedly supplied them with false information
before the raid.
Radio profits
SCOTLAND'S newest radio station, Scot FM, is heading for an operational profit
for the first time, it was announced at the annual meeting yesterday.
Naval ceremony
CARDINAL Thomas Winning will celebrate the Mass of Christmas with Service
personnel and their families from the Clyde Naval Base at Faslane. The naval
base accommodates Britain's nuclear deterrent, the Trident submarine fleet.
Death case
A MAN has been interviewed by police and a report has gone to the fiscal after
the death of Johnstone grandfather John McGrorey. Mr McGrorey, 39, was found
lying in a pool of blood five days ago and later died in hospital.
</TEXT>
