<HEADLINE>ON THE RIGHT SCENT</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Anvar Khan</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>13</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Features</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974749759</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Sex Appeal Rating: HHH
Product: Jean Paul Gaultier
Price: Eau de Toilette Spray #35 (50ml), #50 (100ml); Parfum #98 (30ml)
Description: Popular among 40 to 60 year olds. Gaultier wanted the fragrance to
smell edible, like a French pastry. Product comes in a blank soup tin. Top half
of the bottle is sculpted into the shape of a woman's body in a bustiere
David: Is that a tin of Spam?
Lesley: A masculine packaging, but a very feminine bottle inside. The perfume
looks like pink champagne. The feminists would go mad, that a woman's body has
been used in this commercial way. It reminds me of vanilla, of home-baking. For
office girls, safe and nice.
Naila: Ostentatious but humorous. This is humid, dizzy and motherly, like
tropical flowers from the Botanic Gardens in Glasgow. I can imagine big women
wearing it.
David: If you think of the various perfume bottles over the years, this is very
different. The scent calms down nicely. I'd like this on a woman's neck.
Sex Appeal Rating: HH
Product: Gio by Giorgio Armani
Price: Starts at #19.95 for 30ml, then #23.50 and #35
Description: Bog-standard Italian effort. For women, but our panel thought it
was an aftershave.
Naila: Talcum powder, nae class. I wouldn't trust a man who smelt like this.
Lesley: It hasn't any layers, a monotonous smell, very synthetic. You'd imagine
deadly nightshade smelling like this. Unsettling.
David: I smell violets, what my mother used to wear, so to me this is a
maternal smell. I like it, although it reminds me of Fahrenheit aftershave.
Sex Appeal Rating: H
Product: L'Eau d'Issey for women by Issey Miyake
Price: Eau de Toilette Spray 50ml #35 or 100ml #48, Parfum 15ml #73
Description: The Issey Miyake woman wants a perfume which ``lets her be
herself, adapts to her joys as well as her sorrows''. Miyake says the teardrop
shaped product is ``water suspended in pure, transparent glass''.
David: This looks like a specimen bottle and smells like a sauna cabin before
you turn on the heat.
Lesley: It looks like one of the Three Wise Men. It smells of Creamola Foam or
sherbet. It's very light. You used to call this toilet water. A man would smell
clean wearing it.
Naila: The bottle reminds me of a weapon. It brings back memories of a
ski-resort I once visited. It has a chemical smell, quite refreshing like an
alpine forest.
Sex Appeal rating: H
Product: Dolce Vita
Price: #33 (50ml) and #49
Description: A pleasant eau de toilette for women.
David: Smells like an aftershave and lasts a while.
Lesley: There's a factor out of step, a note that jars - a sweet note then a
chemical note. Not very raunchy.
Naila: Sugared almonds, cherry drops, anything to do with sweeties. A happy
smell. I'd buy it if I couldn't find anything else.
Sex Appeal Rating: H
Product: Cacharel pour L'homme
Price: #19.95 for 50ml
Description: Brown-black packaged aftershave for men. For any sad case who
wants to be regarded as dark and enticing
David: Smells like a mixture of washing-up liquid and fruitcake.
Naila: At first it's curry and pot-pourri, then orange peel and cloves. Exotic.
Lesley: Horrible, smells like those tablets you stick on the side of the
toilet. Lemon Jif.
Sex Appeal Rating: HH
Product: Polo by Ralph Lauren
Price: #18 for 50ml
Description: Unsophisticated aftershave for the sedentary.
Lesley: Naff and unpleasant. Indistinctive.
Naila: Smells masculine and nouveau riche, but friendly.
David: Good for counteracting sweat. Musky. A sporting fragrance like Lynx body
spray.
Sex Appeal Rating: Forget it.
Product: Fleur by Givenchy
Price: #17.50 for 50ml Parfum
Description: Reasonably cheap if not inspiring flowery scent for women.
Naila: Ooof, detergent. This reminds me of doggy shampoo.
David: Someone's got a sense of humour. This is stinking. Smells like wood
resin. It's getting worse, I'm going to wash my hands.
Lesley: Raw, it hits you right on the nose.
Sex Appeal Rating: Nope.
Product: L'Eau d'Issey pour homme by Issey Miyake
Price: After Shave #24 (100ml), Eau de Toilette Spray #38 (125ml)
Description: Stark, chilly, pretentious and minimalist. An angular bottle which
thins at one end. For the anally-retentive only.
Naila: The shape of the bottle reminds me of the remote control for the telly.
It smells rancid, like lard or fat.
Lesley: It smells like human sweat. Maybe it's intended as an aphrodisiac.
David: You could use the bottle as a wedge for the door.
n.Many Thanks to our panel of consumers; David Ewing, Naila Khan and Lesley
Janet Brown. All fragrances are available from Debenhams and Frasers, Glasgow.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951223-000062</DOCNO>
