<HEADLINE>A lone voice</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974749762</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
IT is a difficult time of year for many, single parents, the homeless, etc, but
spare a thought also for the pagan republican who does not gamble.
Those of us with no interest in Christmas, the royal family, or the National
Lottery are, more than ever, strangers in a strange land at this time.
Derek Gibson
42 Marywood Square,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
