<HEADLINE>William Cavaye</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974749775</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
William Torrance Cavaye; born February 5, 1929, died December 11, 1995
THE well-known Edinburgh businessman, Mr Bill Cavaye, has died suddenly in
hospital in the city. He was 66.
Born in Edinburgh in 1929, he was educated at the Royal High School and joined
his family's firm of MacGregor &amp; Company, distributors of glass and china, in
1948. He took over as managing director from his father in 1973.
His commitment to his business was legendary throughout the licensed and
catering trades. He took MacGregor's from a one-showroom enterprise in Leith
Walk to its current standing with branches in Glasgow, Inverness, Gateshead,
and Aberdeen. He retired two years ago and was chairman of the company at the
time of his death.
Beyond his business, Bill Cavaye had many interests. He was a past moderator of
the High Constables of Edinburgh, a past president of Leith Rotary Club, and a
senator of the Junior Chamber International. He was a steward at Murrayfield
for 40 years before the stadium was reconstructed.
He is survived by his wife and two sons and a daughter.
</TEXT>
