<HEADLINE>Seed potato innovation award</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974749805</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LEADING Scottish seed potato producer Gordon &amp; Innes Ltd, which has bases at
Elgin, Huntly and Banff, has won an export innovation award for its work in
tailoring seed to meet the specific requirements of overseas markets.
The award, sponsored by the Potato Marketing Board and organised by Food from
Britain, recognises the substantial growth of the company's export markets.
Gordon &amp; Innes exports seed potatoes to 23 countries, and overseas sales
represent more than 34% of total sales.
To meet the needs of overseas customers, the company has a dedicated department
which carries out detailed local research. This may lead to modifications in
the size of seed or to the delivery date. In the Far East customers require
delivery much earlier than in other markets. Gordon &amp; Innes has developed
growing techniques which provide early harvesting to meet the Far East demand.
</TEXT>
