<HEADLINE>An early review for Ferguson</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>26</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974749826</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EVERTON striker Duncan Ferguson will know the outcome of a judicial review to
determine his immediate future next month. The hearing, granted at the club's
request on the grounds of `double jeopardy,' will now take place on January 19
and not in March as expected.
Everton claim that Ferguson will have been punished twice for the same
head-butting offence if he is forced to complete a Scottish FA imposed ban,
having already spent six weeks in prison.
If the claim is not upheld, he will have to serve out the remaining seven games
of a 12 match ban.
Meanwhile, flu has ruled Ferguson out of today's Premiership trip to Coventry.
</TEXT>
