<TEXT>
Hollywood 95/Royal SNO (Varese Sarabande)
q NEW venture for the Royal Scottish National Orchestra. Recorded in Glasgow's
City Hall in mid-September, with the orchestra under the direction of Hollywood
composer Joel McNeely, this is a vivid, full-blooded set of contemporary scores
for Hollywood films.
And I mean contemporary - bang up to date, with soundtracks from Batman
Forever, Apollo 13, Judge Dredd, Caspar, First Knight, Waterworld, and the
evocative end-title sequence from Braveheart. The single exception is the theme
music to Alexander Korda's 1940 film, That Hamilton Woman, written by Miklos
Rozsa, who died this year, and recorded here as a tribute to one of the most
prolific of film music composers.
</TEXT>
