<TEXT>
n FROM selected stores around the UK, a seasonal gift. The diamante snowman
hails (s'cuse the pun) from the Attwood Collection of hand-crafted costume
jewellery.
It is made of Austrian crystals and an emerald enamelled scarf, set in triple
plated 22 carat gold.
It comes with a lifetime guarantee. Order from Attwood at Kingston-Upon-Thames
on 0181 547 3331. Price #69.25.
n Holding Back the Years: make-up worn at 25 will almost certainly be redundant
at 55. Serums help to create an immediate plumping and tightening effect which
lasts several hours. Concealer is a vital weapon. To make it undetectable,
apply it with the tip of the middle finger and repeatedly tap under the eyes,
over blemishes and broken capillaries. The lighter and creamier the product the
better. Dust with powder.
Choose moisturising or light-reflecting foundations, stay away from matt
formations. Most light-reflecting foundations contain silicone which creates a
smooth surface and does not clump into wrinkles or dry patches.
A heavy foundation will make you look older, so be soft and subtle as possible.
Stick to pale colours of eye shadow and blusher and avoid harsh lines. Pink on
the face is the softest.
They say that three things must go up as you age: your hair, your eyes and your
bosom. Steer clear of a hairstyle which surrounds the face. Hair pulled back is
flattering and takes years off you.
When, also, hair goes grey, its natural colour may no longer suit you. If you
dye it, stick to softer tones that will not harden the face.
</TEXT>
