<TEXT>
Richard Jarman, director of Scottish Opera, who this year announced drastic
measures to save money, putting the organisation on a ``part-time'' footing:
n ``I'm a total Scrooge. I hate absolutely everything to do with Christmas, so
my best Christmas present would be to be put into a deep trance from December
1st to the 27th so I never, ever have to see a Christmas tree, Santa Claus,
decorations or anything. Having woken from the deep trance I would like my
present to be proper funding for Scottish Opera.''
</TEXT>
