<TEXT>
n MEMBER of the International Society for Krishna Consciousness (Hari Krishna)
whose Scottish temple is in Lesmahagow:
We have three major festivals in the year, but Christmas isn't one of them - so
December 25 is just another day for us.
We'll get up at around 4am as usual, then get on with our work of taking the
message of Krishna out to the  people, most of whom will be staying at home.
That means knocking on doors, but on Christmas Day you're never sure what kind
of reception you'll get. Some people invite us in, others shout `Don't you know
what day this is?' and slam the door.
</TEXT>
