<TEXT>
n SPOKESPERSON, the Scottish Prison Service
Prisoners get up at eight instead of seven on Christmas Day and can have a
cooked breakfast. There are services in the chapel followed by recreational
activities. Lunch is standard Christmas fare with all the trimmings, then a
light tea and lock-up fairly early, 5pm instead of 7.30 or 8.o`clock so that
prison officers can get home and be with their families. There is no prison
visiting on the 25th because so many people rely on public transport but there
is extra visiting over the rest of the holiday.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
