Waste incinerator
fails pollution test
AN incinerator which burns half of Scotland's clinical waste has failed a
Government pollution test for the fourth time this year. Inspectors announced
yesterday the level of dust emissions from the Baldovie incinerator in Dundee
was 50% above recommended levels.
Dundee District Council said defective monitoring equipment would be replaced
before a February 16 deadline imposed by inspectors.
Extended hours
THE Asda store in Portobello, Edinburgh, was prepared last night for a 40-hour
trading session. It opened yesterday morning and will not close again until
midnight tonight to accommodate Christmas shoppers.
Surgical break
THE surgical ward of the Western Isles Hospital at Stornoway closed yesterday
for a 10-day period over Christmas. General manager Brian Liddle said staff
would be kept on stand-by in case of emergencies..
Bagpipes stolen
ORGANISERS of a Highland music exhibition at Inverness are appealing for the
return of antique Henderson Drone bagpipes which were stolen on Thursday
afternoon.
</TEXT>
