<TEXT>
n SPOKESWOMAN for the Jewish Information and Resource Centre in Glasgow:
The 25th of December will just be a normal day for Orthodox Jews in Scotland
except that we won't be going to work and the television will be better.
Obviously children are affected by all the Christmas activities going on, but
they learn to adjust. In fact, we have our own festival of Chanukah at this
time of year when we light candles every night for eight days and the children
get little presents and small amounts of money.
