BASHIR Mann, official spokesperson for the Muslim community in Glasgow
n ``We'll be having a day off like everyone else and enjoying some television
and the children may get a few gifts because even though you explain to them
that we have our own festivals, they see these celebrations going on all around
them. First generation Muslims, certainly, respect Christ as a very great
prophet and it's a pity that the day set aside to celebrate his birth seems to
have been taken over by material excess. Personally, I'll be spending the
Christmas period at my ancestral village in Pakistan with my father who is 95.''
